cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or data, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "ARRIVAL Protocol: Structured Semantic Coordination Enables Sustainable Cross-Architecture AI Cooperation"
abstract: >-
  ARRIVAL (Atomic Reasoning via Rival Validation and Adversarial Logic) is a
  structured multi-agent coordination protocol that enables cross-architecture
  LLM ensembles to solve graduate-level scientific questions, practical tasks,
  and game-theoretic cooperation problems through 66 semantic @-atoms and
  CRDT-based conflict resolution. Validated across 2,200+ experiments on 17
  LLM architectures for under $95 total. Key results: 86.4% GPQA Diamond
  via Confidence-Gated Debate (CGD), 0% to 100% GovSim survival (Fisher
  p = 0.008), MEANING-CRDT v1.1 with 11 theorems.
